4.2.1 Account Authentication Alternatives
If a platform, app, or website requires account authentication, the user flow must include additional authentication methods besides the manual input of a password.

4.2.1-A
All platforms, apps, and websites must provide account authentication through manual password entry and alternative, accessible methods including, but not limited to, randomly-generated SMS or email verification codes, mobile app verification, QR code verification (QR codes must not be the only additional method since they are inaccessible for people with vision impairments).

4.2.1-B
No platforms, apps, or websites may utilize cognitive function tests as part of their account authentication or creation flows as specified in section 3.3.2.
